The paper discusses the evolution of Simultaneous Localisation and Mapping (SLAM) into a general geometric and semantic 'Spatial AI' perception capability for intelligent embodied devices. This involves the co-design of algorithms, processors, and sensors. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO), Computer Vision (cs.CV), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
